			<title>Cloning Tool</title>
			<link>http://www.sigsiu.net/download/tools/cloning_tool.html</link>
			<description> Bash script to clone SOBI2 and all possible add-ons.
 

Usage instructions: 

Extract SOBI2 (or plugin or module etc) into a temporary directory
Copy the attached script (and unpack of course) also into this temporary directory
From the console (terminal) execute sh clone_sobi.sh
Follow the further instructions of the script




Sigrids-Mac:clone trinity$ sh clone_sobi.sh 
 
SOBI2 Cloning Tool 
Copyright by Sigsiu.NET, 2009 
----------------------------- 
First enter the name of your SOBI2 clone. 
Even if you clone a plugin or module, enter the name of the SOBI2 clone. 
 
Enter now the name of your clone: 
sigrid 
Parsing ./admin.category.class.html.php 
..... 
Parsing ./toolbar.sobi2.php 
Parsing ./uninstall.sobi2.php 
 
Enter component menu description (as shown in your Joomla! admin menu): 
Sigrid's Directory 
Renaming ./admin.sobi2.cats.php to ./admin.sigrid.cats.php 
Renaming ./admin.sobi2.class.html.php to ./admin.sigrid.class.html.php 
..... 
Renaming ./uninstall.sobi2.php to ./uninstall.sigrid.php 
 
Done. 
New clone installation for SOBI2 created. The name of the clone is sigrid. 
Pack the content of the folder into a ZIP package. 
Install the package in your Mambo/Joomla!/SOBI2 installation. 
 </description>
